.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-CLEAN" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.21" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-clean \- Remove old tracked job directories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose clean [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Preview or remove tracked job metadata and runtime directories for the active compose context while keeping recent tracking data available.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--age\fR \fIDAYS\fR
Remove tracked job directories older than this many days.
.TP
\fB--all\fR
Remove all tracked job directories except the latest one.
.TP
\fB--dry\-run\fR
Preview the tracked job cleanup plan without deleting files.
.TP
\fB--disk\-usage\fR
Include recursive disk\-usage totals for tracked job paths.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose clean \-\-age 7
hpc\-compose clean \-\-all \-\-dry\-run
hpc\-compose clean \-\-all \-\-format json
.fi
